(Translated by Google) Very rich Ramen !!!  (Original) Muy rico Ramen!!!

Amazing little ramen restaurant. We ate here last night and enjoyed every aspect of it. The place is really clean with friendly staff that are really helpful and attentive. The menu is moderately sized and as the name suggests, predominantly ramen with a few curry dishes in there. We ordered the Tonkatsu Shoyu ramen, the Katsu curry and some popcorn chicken as a side. We really underestimated the portion sizes as they were huge and we deffinately ordered too much food. Regardless of this, everything we ordered was great, full of flavor and really filling.

The food and drinks were really good however the service was horrid. The waitresses always seemed bothered to do anything for us like getting a glass of water. Whenever we called them, they simply ignored us and kept going about whatever  job they were doing.  Was quite a let down as it was my partners 21st birthday.
Nice ramen in the heart of waikkiki.
Excellent restaurant. Atmosphere, service and ramen are great.
Food is good. The restaurant adds 16% gratuity to your bill just as a heads up.

Goma Tei Ramen is located inside the International Marketplace on the 3rd Floor. After reading many raved reviews, I definitely had to check it out. I tried the SunHo Ramen, which had a hot spicy sour broth, which was definitely different; but their ramen noodles felt very authentic compared to the other ramen offered in Waikiki. For ~$15 a bowl, it was nothing fantastic, and I wouldn't recommend driving out of my way to come here. The only thing I felt was that was going for them is their spacious restaurant which is good for big groups, and the portion size of the ramen bowls were huge. There is also a 16% service charge for groups of 6 or more.

Completely unsatisfied. Took our char siu fried rice leftover home only to find a piece of plastic wrap hidden in the rice. This was for our toddler; hopefully, he didn't consume any poisonous plastic material while at the restaurant. Unfortunately, and gladly, threw away the leftover. We are done with this place.

Not very vegan friendly. They have two dishes which is appreciated. The non spicy dish is what I ordered and the flavor was just not good. It said a soy and scallion flavor, but it tasted heavy and bitter. It had a thick layer of what looked like some sort of fat on top and I didn’t recognize half of the veggies and they didn’t have tofu. The servers were friendly and very thankful and polite so I gave two stars.
Another first time eating here. I got the Chicken shoyo and it was good. I will be returning here whenever we are in Hawaii.

I came in to try the truffle ramen...it's more subtle than I expected, the flavor of the noodles is subdued...you notice the aroma of truffles more than taste it. It comes with three pieces of (I'm still trying to figure it out), mushrooms, greens and a perfect soft boiled egg. I liked it but didn't love it... it's back to Tan Tan ramen for me.
Shoyu chicken ramen is delicious 😋

Service was excellent which is why I gave it 2 stars instead of 1. The people were great. The food? Awful. It had no flavor and the wontons were slightly undercooked. Now I understand why they add gratuity ahead of time. (Though again the staff was great and I upped the tip to 20% as normal). I’ll skip this place in future though. Marekame Udon is just across the street and way better.

(Translated by Google) There is a queue all day and the reason is that the prices are normal and the ramen is homemade. Not bad if you don't want to spend a fortune on food (as usual in Hawaii)  (Original) C’è da fare la fila tutto il giorno e il motivo è che i prezzi sono normali e il ramen è fatto in casa. Non male se non si vuole spendere un patrimonio per mangiare (come al solito alle Hawaii)

One of the better tasting ramen around Waikiki, but still, their other ramen restaurant at Ala Moana has better broth and more tender noodles...so 3 star  Staff are nice enough and attentive, okay interior and clean seatings ...5 star  Automatic gratuity 16% is ridiculous and rude (I’m willing to pay tips for good service). And worst of all there was an additional line for tip...1 star  Average... 3 star.  They are doing it totally wrong. One tan tan ramen costed $15.27. With that taste, I would be more than happy to pay $15.27 for ramen alone! And I would add some tips additional. But with automatic gratuity, I felt I don’t need to.

Goma Tei has some pretty good ramen. If you're in Waikiki, be sure to visit. They also have curry, udon, and combination plates. The restaurant is on the 3rd floor near all the other restaurants, and they will validate your ticket. The staff is friendly and nice. They cannot split the bill, but can half it, and tip is already included. If you're kama'aina, let them know and they'll hook you up. Great place to visit and catch up with friends. My favorite is the char siu tan tan ramen.
Nothing too spectacular. Ramen was too soft for my liking and the chashu was mediocre. Gyoza and vegetable was not great either.
Great Ramen, great service. Excellent location. Definitely would come back
The food is good, but expensive since it's in Waikiki. Cheaper to go to their other locations and food is just as good.
(Translated by Google) I missed Japanese food and came to eat something simple. The truffle gyoza seems to be delicious.  (Original) 日本食が恋しくなってあっさりしたものを食べに来てしまった。トリュフ餃子がおいしいらしい。
Good food
16% tip was automatically included for my wife and I which is ridiculous.
Actually should be 3 1/2 stars. The place is really cozy and clean. Staff very friendly. The Tan Tan Ramen is little spicy. Shoyu is not spicy.
Good ramen and gyoza ! BUT the gyoza a bit like chinese dumpling!!!!
Not the best ramen I have eaten...I wouldn't recommend
Very good ramen. Fast service
Ramen was fresh and filling, but lacking in flavor

Our server said 16% of gratuity would be automatically added to our bill. I didn't care because I work at hospitality industry and usually leave 20% tip unless service is extremely terrible. However, All our server did was taking order, bringing food and (different server) bringing our bill before we even finished out meal. They never came back to check on how we were doing, didn't pre bus our table, not even come back to pick up our check, so we had to go to host station to pay. The place was slow, and FOH staffs were just shooting the breeze in the dining room. They probably thought they didn't have to do any work since tip’s already added, but Adding gratuity with no service is same as charging food for what people didn't even eat.

Excellent food here. I had the pork ramen noodle bowl. Really tasty and not salty like some are. Wasn't thirsty afterwards ! Friendly waitress who asked me if I wanted a fork because I was struggling with the sticks. Will be going back before we leave. Just there in Oct 2019. Still very good food and service. Priced right too.
Good soup!
The food was great but we eat there at noon and I think the AC was off or not working.
I don't like it. In addition expensive.
FOOD was not up to par. Gyoza was not completely cooked.
Delicious food. Customizable meals. Great service. Lots of variety. Only one shortcoming-no coffee or plain, unsweetened tea.
Ramen itself was very bland. Not what I would expect from true Japanese cooking.....

I like this place because of the freshly made in-house noodles! There's a service charge of 16% added to the bill. It's obvious because of the machine they have in the back that makes their noodles. I also like this place because of the kama'aina discount. I recommend their ban ban ji chicken, chicken tatsutage, or the goma wings. I like chicken that's why!

Our party of four came in for a late lunch at around 2:30 on a Monday and the restaurant was completely empty. Not sure if this is the norm or if we just came at a weird hour. Even so, it took a while for them, each time we needed something.  We started out with the Chicken Tatsutaage as an appetizer. It comes with a dipping sauce on the side but the seasoning on the chicken is already salty/flavorful enough. I liked that it was bitesize, like popcorn chicken, so it was a lot easier to eat.  For my main, I had the garlic tan tan ramen, which I believe was one of their seasonal specials. It comes with char siu, some veggies, and a bed of garlic resting on top of a sheet of seaweed. It wasn't bad but I think the garlic really made it. If it was plain, it wouldn't have been anything special.  Probably wouldn't come back. I'm sure there are tons of other ramen spots in Hawaii, and I'd like to try those first.
There is a 15% Kama'aina discount offered here along with a 16% charge added to the bill that includes tax and tip. There was no wait around 7pm and fast, friendly service.
Yum

Very good selection of ramen and curry. The specials were excellent and the portions were just right. Spicy Tan Tan was spicy, level 3 was just the right amount of spicy. The service was attentive without being disruptive. Try the Japanese won tons, delicious.

Food was pretty good. The truffle taken didn't quite meet my expectations, but the popcorn chicken was awesome. I wish my server had more energy and not thrilled about the mandatory 16% gratuity. I know they have it in place since some from other cultures may not tip, but if it's not common with the other restaurants, it's not a good thing to be there only one doing it.
Service was a little slow especially had a long wait for the check but food was very tasty!

Ramen was OK. Seated us in a hallway-like place even though the main eating area, which was much nicer, had lots of seats available. Service was not attentive but they automatically add a tip for all parties, not just large parties. So the tip doesn't reward good service like at almost all other restaurants.
Goma Tei always delivers when I'm craving Ramen. You can't go wrong.
Excellent Ramen
Always good for ramen. They send to always have new items to choose from lately.

Very delicious, filling, and reasonably priced. Their dishes are delicious hot or cold.
Awesome food excellent.
Loved this place!! Awesome vegan/vegetarian options, and really good flavors in their ramen dishes!

OMG! The broth!!! Divine! Rich and creamy! Savory pork flavor with notes of peanut and a hint of spice. Perfect noodles, thin and chewy. The char-shu pork was tender and flavorful. The gyozas were amazing! Plump with pork and veggies. Make your own dipping sauce with soy sauce, pepper spices and a little vinegar. Gratuity is included at this location, but they were very attentive and deserving. Note: draft beer and prior cocktails may have influenced this review. ;)
So they told us it's a forced gratuity of 16% then the server decides to give us the worst service. She wasn't helpful, didn't provide options and was just rude. We walked out and went elsewhere.
good is good and inexpensive for waikiki international marketplace. they have kamaaina discount but automatically add gratuity to the bill which i don't think it's right.
Absolute worst ramen and food I’ve ever had. Inedible food.
The place was clean, and servers were servers were nice. But the food was a little bit bland.

This ramen was one of my favorite meals on Hawai'i. I got the spicy version of the basic pork dish and it was perfectly hot, the pork was tender and the broth oozing with flavor. Loved it and told my irritated family 100 times!

Food is always made quickly and consistently good.

This restaurant pick money directly in my pocket. They force to pay a 16% gratuity. The food was ordinary, the service was great. But this forced gratuity is totally a non. The server told me it is because some nationality do not tip. Witch is actually the case of Japan. AND THIS IS A JAPANE RESTAURANT!!! This is totally a non sence. I usually tip when the service is good, but a forced gratuity... I hate that. I should have refuse to pay it. This would deserve 0 star but it's not possible.

I wouldn't say I had the worst ramen ever because I don't even consider this ramen. Noodle is rubbery, broth is bland, chicken is bland, vegetable is bland, it was a bowl of bland something. Flavor of noodle and broth was more like soba than ramen. Supposedly this was a special truffle ramen, but there was not even a scent of it, definitely not worth $20. Automatic 16% tip is fine, and the servers were super nice. But I don't think there is a single Japanese person working there. It's Chinese owned business.

This place has AMAZING customer service! At first I was a little skeptical of the prices, but after eating here I thought that they were amazing prices for the portions! Amazing food and you should try the truffle ramen which is inexpensive and delicious!

We loved eating here when we're visiting Hawaii. My husband couldn't get enough of their ramen! All kinds to choose from and also delicious curry! The staff was friendly and the inside was stylish with comfortable seating. Definitely a place we'll remember for their tasty food 😋

Nice atmosphere, and good food. The pork was SO tender, in the Tan Tan Ramen, but the broth tastes/smells like it has a peanut base, and I wasn't a huge fan. Their curry is amazing  though! Enjoyed a delicious milk tea following lunch.
My curry ramen was pretty good.
Amazing food! Food is flavorful and delicious. Staff are friendly and very kind. Restaurant is clean and welcoming.

I really enjoyed my chicken spicy (not as spicy as I expected) ramen. The waitress said this was enough for one person as I wanted to order Gyoza as well. She was honest with her opinion on my selection. I arrived late after an expensive small meal I had at a Japanese food  hall nearby... I was able to grab dinner (again) from here at 9:30pm and was fulfilled. Must try and prices are very reasonable $9-15USD. I had the lemon ice tea which was nice but quite strong in taste. 5 stars for quick, polite, great price for fresh quality and tasty dish.
Great tasting ramen and great prices for servings
Good was great and staff was friendly!
The ramen was great!! The noodles are really good. They make their noodles with a special machine and it tastes amazing. Great service and a friendly staff made our lunch memorable.

Was hungry for ramen and they were there and I was tired of walking. The food was good, but nothing special. Lunch prices were good, but got very turned off when told by the waitress that they automatically added a service/tip charge of 16% to the bill.  Staff were friendly and the location clean and decent, but again, nothing special.  I am not going to say it was a bad experience and it did satisfy my hunger at the moment, but it definitely doesn't deserve more then a 3 star for my overall experience. Oh, one other irrigating thing associated to the added service/tip charge of 16%, there as a tip line for additional tip.

A group of us came here on a weekday evening. It wasn’t busy so we got seats right away and the service was good. Everyone was satisfied with their meals. I really liked the teriyaki chicken rice bowl I ordered which had a fried egg on top. It was comfort food for me. My wife ordered the seafood shoyu ramen which was also very good. The broth was very tasty (she got the non-spicy) and the noodles were cooked just right (not too soft). We definitely enjoyed it here. Just remember that they charge the gratuity on the bill. Not my preference since it kind of pushes the labour cost to the customer; however, the prices are reasonable for the location in Waikiki beach.
Generous serving size we had the ramen and chicken katsu curry both full of flavour. Well priced considering the location. The waiters were friendly enough and the tips already built into the bill.

Serving size were generous for the price, considering location. Service was unexpectedly slow. We had the wakame ramen and loco moco curry. Both were competently executed. Overall, I had no regrets eating here, but I would not bring my friends or family here at some future time.

I tried the char siu tantanmen ramen. The char siu was very soft, the noodles were very firm which i like. I was kinda surprised to find a good ramen place here in Honolulu but then i remembered that there are many Japanese people around.

I like their basic curry (chicken) a lot.  Very large portion, tasty, not too spicy but can be requested hotter or add chili oil from the little jar.  Chicken wings were not to my taste, but YMMV.  Reasonable price for Waikiki.  I've eaten here 3 or 4 times now.  Have not tried other dishes though. Note that 16% gratuity is mandatory.  Service was very fast.
Tan tan ramen place. I've noticed that hawaii have couple restaurants that charge tips automatically and this is one of them (16%). Food was ok and service was decent.
(Translated by Google) Very good ramen, I liked less cold tea and gyozas.  (Original) Très bons ramens, j'ai moins aimé le thé froid et les gyozas.

A well situated and well priced Japanese resturant that serves meals that are of a high quality and size. I had a traditional style ramen with pork that just fell apart and gyoza the equal of any I've had in Japan.  Would definitely recommend
Perfect noodles, excellent broth, fast service. Don't miss this treat!
Amazing food, very friendly staff that are helpful with everything

Good food and good service but they impose a 16% tip on any size group.  I won't go back there!  If that's the model they want then pay your employees a decent wage and put that cost in the price of your food.

(Original) Muy delicioso comida Goma Tei del Estilo Japones , recomiendo el Ramen con Mariscos (SeaFoo Tan Tan) , y también para los Vegetarianos el Ramen con Vegetales (Vegetable Tan Tan) , hay platos para los amantes de Picantes.
Good atmosphere and clean place. The noodles were tasty and broth good but the toppings left little to be desired.

My wife and I had a great time! The ambiance was fantastic. The service was great. We ordered the new the pork belly tan tan and another pork belly ramon dish. We also had an order of goyza. Everything was out in a reasonable time and tasted great! Are only issue and it was hardly an issue was that is was on the higher price end for ramon. Overall however would recommend to everyone looking for a good ramon in the city!

Friendly staff. Clean and simple design. We were seated right away. They tell you right off that a 16% gratuity is included in the bill, which is ok as long as they deserved it. I ordered the seafood fried rice and my wife ordered the chicken shoyu ramen. I also ordered the goma chicken wings. The fried rice was quite delicious and the seafood was cooked right. The soft boiled egg was good. The chicken wings were delicious with a wonderful crunchy exterior and moist interior. The ginger sesame based sauce was a wonderful addition. The ramen had tender chicken bits and the vegetables were tender and the broth flavorful. The ramen was perfectly cooked. The wait for the food wasn't bad at all. A good experience.
Delicious foods here and huge portions

I enjoyed my food, the staff were very friendly. Place was clean. My ramen was weak in flavor but it was still tasty. It wasn't as mind blowing as I was told. Also they add an 16-18% gratuity regardless of party size.
Great
Excellent Tan Tan Ramen
Really good ramen place in Waikiki. Portion is huge, btw.

(Translated by Google) Don't expect the ramen taste that is common in Korea. It's basically peanut butter, so the oily taste is doubled, and it's subtly flavored with 2% of something that tastes subtly Japanese ramen. Liver). But the taste itself is not so bad when eaten. The amount of chashu is especially high .. But it doesn't taste like you want to come back later. Also, the big problem is the price is very expensive. There are so many things that you can't eat it if you have two people. (It's not too much for the price ..) Moreover, the tip cost is automatically included 16%, and the bill comes out. It's not particularly good service, but it's not good to be forced. If you give a tip again, you'll double. Tasty ramen and gyoza. Good value, efficient service
Not bad
Ramen is good , service good , just expensive (but is Hawain)the only thing I did not like is the charge service fee no matter how many people!!

This place looks clean and fancy. foods are large in portion at a decent price. the 3-piece meat version of ramen is way too much for me. the base soup of ramen is totally different from the “thick” traditional Japanese ramen .  Since the waitress desperately tried to convince us to try their new truffle ramen ($20), we ordered one and it does taste better but the noodle came at a much smaller portion!  At first my kids refused to try the new truffle ramen , the waitress came back and asked them “Why not?”,” is it the higher price?”,etc. I guess this is the Asian way to do market research but to Americans like my kids it was a very rude manner .  Hope their branch at ala moana has better service.

Maybe just me, but I disliked the food. My ramen tasted like peanut butter?? The teriyaki chicken tasted a bit off and chewy. Curry rice tasted okay, not really good. Don’t order the raspberry ice tea because it tastes so sugary that it makes me want to throw it out and flush it in the toilet.

It is a restaurant open in the popular International Market Place with decent decor.  Service was fairly good therefore I was, kind of, ok with the mandatory 16% service charge that was applied to the bill.  However, the food, even a simple shoyu ramen was really subpar.  The soup was tasteless and the ramen was not chewy.  The funny thing was to have Chinese Choy Sum as a part of it.  This makes me wonder if this restaurant should have called itself Goma Tai Fusion Ramen instead.    Location-deco-service-food... The kitchen should have done a better job.

Food was actually quite good. Trying ramen first time good impressions but I know there are still much more better ramen out there. Waiters were nice and attended here and there. When we asked if ice tea had refills old gentleman said no and that soft drinks only have two max refill. Overall it was a good experience but they charge 16% for gratitude. That’s the problem way too expensive and the customer should have the choice to decide how much they want to tip. Say if the waiters didn’t do good job and lacked great service and you still were charged the same price of a tip. “I think da fuq not” . Plus it’s kind of a riff off to any foreigner who don’t know that the gratitude fee is a fancy way of rephrasing “tip”.
It's okay. But for ramen lovers, I can see why this place is great.
Best ramen in Waikiki

Everything on the menu looks good and reasonably priced
Enjoy the ramen. I’m sensitive to MSG and even though they admit there is some in the broth I can finish the whole thing without it bothering me. Nice place away from the crowds. I go often.

Had the privilege of trying this little gem during my last visit to Hawaii. Being a SoCal girl, I thought I had tried the best ramen outside of Japan. But I was sooo wrong. The selection that Goma Tei offers is amazing!!!!! I ordered the Ramen Tonkatsu. Never thought I could have ramen and tonkatsu in one dish. I was a happy girl!!!! The broth was rich, the ramen was cooked perfectly and the tonkatsu was crispy (10/10).  The restaurant is very clean and the staff is very helpful. I can't wait to go back to Hawaii to eat at Goma Tei Ramen.
Delicious and great service!
We are Raman Fan ,we like try different famous Raman over the world ,This Raman not real Japanese Raman Beware they add 16% tip on your bill ,don’t pay double !
Good, fast and very affordable for Waikiki.  Quality and quantity is good.

Hidden gem. Reasonable Japanese ramen.  3rd floor new International Marketplace. Noodles a little "firm".... as with traditional Japanese noodle shop, be sure and specify if you want softer noodles. Well worth the trip to the 3rd floor!

Too salty and taste like the instant type.
I was seated and served very quickly. I went for lunch and had a great window table. The ramen had amazing flavor and the pork was falling apart. It was absolutely delicious! The staff was so kind!

Great place, with a good atmosphere. The food was quite tasty and delivered quickly. The place had a steady stream of people coming in even on a late Sunday night. Recommended should you want some ramen in a classy place in Honolulu.
Place was great, service was awesome and food was delish!

It was the first time I tried the ramen and it was OK.  I'm 80% vegetarian, so I tried the vegetarian Tan Tan and I liked it.  The price is reasonable.  It was about $12.  Plus the restaurant is on the top floor so it has a beautiful view.

Service staff was very polite and attentive! Great portion size, though prices were slightly more than I'd pay normally (first meal off the plane). There is a required gratuity/service fee of 16% (you will be reminded before ordering).
The spicy broth is great with the generous amount of ingredients. Overall good experience.
I had the chicken katsu curry and it was delicious!
Superior ramen. Ignore the naysayers.

The food is below average. One thing I noticed was the food is oily, especially the items with noodles. They have floating oil and it smells like spices. Think of a soup with water + oil + spices; I have no idea how my wife had it. Service is average. I had teriyaki chicken and I would consider it one of the worst I have ever had and I have had teriyaki chicken at several places so I feel qualified to judge. Also they add 16% (maybe 18% don't remember) service charge. I didn't bother to leave any extra tip given the horrible food.

Can't say I was all that impressed. Shrimp and squid in my seafood tan tan were overdone. The noodles and broth were alright, though.  The place is trying too hard and looks like a quick stop thing that they made all fancy for no reason. Case in point, nice layout and finishings but with wooden disposable chopsticks. Cheap plastic cups.  They also added 16% service charge just because. So don't add extra tip unless you really want to.  Overall, I wouldn't go back. You can get better for less at many other places nearby.

It was OK to visit, but I wouldn't visit there again nor recommend. Tasty food, but service wasn't good. I ordered a beer but I got it after someone seat down on the table after me get all the dishes including a beer. I'm sure that the staff forget to bring mine. Foods were little overpriced and 16% of tip was included automatically.

Curry meals great - one meal was the Curry loco moco which worked very well! Quick service initially but they forgot my second beer and then charged us for more drinks than the table had. No biggie - was sorted after a while though.

The staff are extremely friendly and very willing to help with the menu items for those of us not familiar with all Japanese dishes. The food arrived quickly and was delicious and the price for its location was very reasonable,  we will definitely return on our next trip to Waikiki.. 😀

I have been to many Ramen places in the mainland but this is one of the worst ones I have ever been to. The portions here are good, but that seems to be the only highlight. I ordered some pan fried dumplings and 2 bowls of noodles. The dumplings taste like frozen food I got from Costco. The pork in ramen is very greasy, too greasy to be tasty. And it was a bit overcooked so not very tender neither. The service is not bad. But I wouldn't go back here and would not recommend anyone to this place.

Very good service, friendly and efficient servers. Ramen comes very quickly! Vegetable shoyu ramen has lots of nutritious greens and mushrooms and broth is very tasty. Been here a few times - consistent quality and good price! 10% off for kamaina :)
